The paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) based approaches for semantic alignment and object landmark detection, which are primarily related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses weakly- or unsupervised learning frameworks, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed joint learning approach involves a loss function that imposes a consistency constraint between the two tasks, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.CL.
